## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="4c6e8-102">El <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.TransformChain> clase contiene una lista de <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.Transform> objetos que determinan cómo ordenar los datos XML antes de crear una síntesis.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="4c6e8-102">The <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.TransformChain> class contains a list of <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.Transform> objects that determine how to order XML data before creating a digest.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="4c6e8-103">Use la <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.TransformChain> clase siempre que tenga que agregar uno o varios objetos de transformación a un documento XML cifrado o a un documento XML firmado.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="4c6e8-103">Use the <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.TransformChain> class whenever you need to add one or more transform objects to an encrypted XML document or to a signed XML document.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="4c6e8-104">Tanto el <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.Reference> clase y la <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.EncryptedReference> clase contienen un <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.TransformChain> objeto.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="4c6e8-104">Both the <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.Reference> class and the <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.EncryptedReference> class contain a <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.TransformChain> object.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="4c6e8-105">Puede agregar un <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.Transform> el objeto a la <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.Reference> clase mediante una llamada a la <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.Reference.AddTransform%2A> método.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="4c6e8-105">You can add a <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.Transform> object to the <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.Reference> class by calling the <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.Reference.AddTransform%2A> method.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="4c6e8-106">Puede agregar un <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.Transform> el objeto a la <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.EncryptedReference> clase mediante una llamada a la <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.EncryptedReference.AddTransform%2A> método.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="4c6e8-106">You can add a <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.Transform> object to the <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.EncryptedReference> class by calling the <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.EncryptedReference.AddTransform%2A> method.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="4c6e8-107">También puede crear un <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.TransformChain> objeto manualmente y pasar a ninguna el <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.Reference.TransformChain%2A> propiedad o <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.EncryptedReference.TransformChain%2A> propiedad.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="4c6e8-107">You can also create a <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.TransformChain> object manually and pass it to either the <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.Reference.TransformChain%2A> property or the <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.EncryptedReference.TransformChain%2A> property.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="4c6e8-108">Si desea iniciar sesión sólo una parte de un documento XML, puede usar una transformación para identificar los elementos XML que se va a iniciar sesión.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="4c6e8-108">If you want to sign only a portion of an XML document, you can use a transform to identify the XML elements you intend to sign.</span></span>  <span data-ttu-id="4c6e8-109">Tenga en cuenta que la <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.Reference.Uri%2A> propiedad y el <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.EncryptedReference.Uri%2A> propiedad crear automáticamente transformaciones internas que le permiten firmar una parte de un documento.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="4c6e8-109">Note that the <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.Reference.Uri%2A> property and the <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.Xml.EncryptedReference.Uri%2A> property automatically create internal transforms that allow you to sign a portion of a document.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="4c6e8-110">Para obtener más información acerca de las transformaciones, vea la especificación XMLDSIG, que está disponible en el W3C en www.w3.org/TR/xmldsig-core/, o vea la especificación de cifrado XML, que está disponible en el W3C en www.w3.org/TR/xmlenc-core/.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="4c6e8-110">For more information about transforms, see the XMLDSIG specification, which is available from the W3C at www.w3.org/TR/xmldsig-core/, or see the XML encryption specification, which is available from the W3C at www.w3.org/TR/xmlenc-core/.</span></span>  
  
 ]]></format>
